post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_3313527_3313543_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.7142857142857143, "section_id": 2420}}, "n3337": {"so_3313527_3313543_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.7142857142857143, "section_id": 2405}}, "n4659": {"so_3313527_3313543_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.7142857142857143, "section_id": 2695}}}, "3313527": {"ViewCount": "156", "Body": "<p>I'm wondering if I need an RAII wrapper around <code>std::fstream</code>....</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "3313543", "Title": "Does allowing a std::fstream to be destroyed close the associated file?", "CreationDate": "2010-07-22T21:10:19.427", "Id": "3313527", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2010-07-22T21:16:58.583", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "82320", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "3313543": {"Id": "3313543", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>No you don't. It closes the file. <code>\u00a7 27.8.1.2</code>:</p>\n<pre><code>virtual \u02dcbasic_filebuf();  \n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_3313527_3313543_0\"><strong>Effects:</strong> Destroys an object of class basic_filebuf. Calls close().</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(which is contained as an object within <code>std::fstream</code> (<code>\u00a7 27.8.1.11</code>), thus being destructed when the <code>fstream</code> is destructed).</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "34509", "LastActivityDate": "2010-07-22T21:16:58.583", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2010-07-22T21:11:58.293", "ParentId": "3313527", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "34509", "LastEditDate": "2010-07-22T21:16:58.583"}});